replies.bodyText:
I verified that when an index ".ml-state-write" exists, one cannot create an alias with the same name:
{
  "error": {
    "root_cause": [
      {
        "type": "invalid_alias_name_exception",
        "reason": "Invalid alias name [.ml-state-write], an index exists with the same name as the alias",
        "index_uuid": "YyvpSSoSQc6yoBq69Q0gDg",
        "index": ".ml-state-write"
      }
    ],
    "type": "invalid_alias_name_exception",
    "reason": "Invalid alias name [.ml-state-write], an index exists with the same name as the alias",
    "index_uuid": "YyvpSSoSQc6yoBq69Q0gDg",
    "index": ".ml-state-write"
  },
  "status": 400
}

So I'd propose to leave the code as it is because this situation (pre-existing .ml-state-write index) is unlikely and could have as well happened before this PR.
An alternative would be to throw an exception if such a situation is detected. WDYT?

